We're excited to launch a new phase of Finders Keepers 🥹 What we're creating here is exactly what I wish existed when I first left college and was working freelance in textiles design. I was working from home on my living room table. Stitching large-scale murals for commercial jobs. Packing and unpacking my tools each morning and evening. There was no end to the working day. Often, I'd end up stitching until all hours of the morning because home was work! 

Fast forward 15 years ⚡️ I feel so lucky to be based in this big building we now call our creative home. So much potential. But there are pockets of this great space that are unused. Design surrounds every element of Finders Keepers. What better way to utilise this space, than to open it up and share it with some other creatives ✨️

If you're in a creative career and feel your current working situation is lacking, find your Mojo, come join our creative space!

Please email us at
Lisa@finderskeepersthestore.ie 
Tell us about you and your work. If you can include photos too that would be great. We would ask that you don't express your interest via DMs and just stick to email 🙏

Please share with anyone you think may be interested. 

Thank you!

Lisa + gang

This week, we celebrate 6 years of Finders Keepers and 1 year of FK on Michael Street! I always feel like our birthday comes at an unfortunate time. It's so chaotic in the lead up to Christmas its kind of impossible to do anything to mark it.

So instead, I've rounded up 10 pictures that tell our story over the past six years 🥰🥰 (some of the pics uploaded wrong so you'll find them up in stories instead 😅)

We're raising a family and raising a business. Is it easy? Absolutely not! But we are embracing the adventure and are so grateful for all the new connections we are making along the way. 

Our main goal when opening this shop, was to bring some magic to Waterford. There was nothing like us here when we opened. A cabinet of curiosity. Always evolving. But with a kind, friendly atmosphere that never falters.

Thank you Beth, this wouldn't be half as fun without you by my side. Who would have thought when we were kids battling it out at home, that we'd end up working together, peas in a pod! And to my sister in law Jess, the best dressed member of our team!!! We love you. Your style, your energy, your talents know no bounds.

To all the wonderful creatives that are stocked in our shop. Thank you for working with us and creating the pieces that make our hearts sing!

We're excited for next year. Breathing new life into the Mojo creative space. Working with our community of shopkeepers in Waterford to make the city wonderful.

Hope to see you over the coming weeks as you pick up your Christmas gifts. This is our time to shine, so please do come in and enjoy the magic! 

All my love
Lisa

So what was in all those boxes last week? 😍😍😍

We're so excited to share our 2024 calendar with you, which showcases a year in Waterford from a new perspective! We worked with local photographers Luke Marsh and Jody Sutton, who used their drones to capture our county from above. Much loved locations you think you know so well, are presented in a whole new light. 

An icy January morning above Reginalds’ tower. Spot the brave, tiny swimmers at The Guillamene in March. The peregrine falcon who nests in Christ Church cathedral steels the show in April. Tramore Sand Dunes giving Mauritius a run for its money in July!

This calendar will be enjoyed by all those with a connection to Waterford, both near and afar. 

This was a collaborative project between Leon Murphy Creative, Jody Sutton Photography and Luke Marsh. Three wonderful talents who have come together and produced something that we know will be enjoyed by so many homes. 

We are thrilled to put this out into the world!

Available in store and online now 🩵

What a number to end the year on. 

I hope and wish that 2024 will bring peace.
 
To see what is happening in the world feels completely surreal. How we can be so safe in one place and how the same humans, can live through such horrors in another. It doesn't make sense. We're all just human. None of us own any of this. We borrow things for the short time we are here. If we treat one another with kindness and respect, two simple things, how different would our world be?

We will continue to shout for a ceasefire. And in our own communities, do the best we can each day for one another. If we do good, it will ripple out to those around us and extend to the wider world. It's simple but it's what I'm choosing to do, so I don't feel so helpless. From little things big things grow. 

Sending love to you all, and wishing nothing but good for you in 2024
